## 5. Media Upload Flow (Images)

### Presigned URL Flow

```
1. Client requests upload URL
   в””в”Җв”Җ POST /api/media/upload-url
   в””в”Җв”Җ Body: { filename, contentType, size }
   
2. Server generates presigned S3 URL
   в””в”Җв”Җ Validates file type/size
   в””в”Җв”Җ Creates Media record (status: pending)
   в””в”Җв”Җ Generates unique S3 key: `uploads/{creatorId}/{uuid}/{filename}`
   в””в”Җв”Җ Returns: { uploadUrl, mediaId, key }
   
3. Client uploads directly to S3
   в””в”Җв”Җ PUT to presigned URL
   в””в”Җв”Җ Bypasses server (efficient for large files)
   
4. Client confirms upload
   в””в”Җв”Җ POST /api/media/confirm
   в””в”Җв”Җ Body: { mediaId, key }
   
5. Server starts processing
   в””в”Җв”Җ Queue image processing job
   в””в”Җв”Җ Generate: thumbnail, multiple sizes, watermarked version
   в””в”Җв”Җ Update Media: processingStatus вҶ’ completed
   в””в”Җв”Җ Store processed URLs
```

### S3 Key Structure

```
nuttyfans-media-{env}/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ uploads/
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ {creatorId}/
в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ {uuid}/
в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ original.jpg
в”Ӯ           в”ңв”Җв”Җ thumb_200x200.jpg
